# Frontend (React)

## API & errors

- Use `apps/web/src/api/client.ts` for all API calls. Do not add raw `fetch` elsewhere without wrapping and error handling.
- Use `getErrorMessage()` from `utils/errors` to show user-facing error messages. Display errors in UI (e.g. under forms), not only in console.
- Handle loading and error states; avoid blank or unstyled placeholders for real content.

## UI

- Use existing components and Tailwind classes. Keep styling consistent with the rest of the app.
- For new pages, add a route in `App.tsx` and navigation in `Layout` if needed.

